==English==

===Etymology===
Believed to be a variation of [[Parthian shot]], a military maneuver in which [[Parthian]] troops retreating on horseback turned back to face the enemy and shot while retreating [http://www.etymonline.com/index.php?term=Parthian], [http://www.phrases.org.uk/bulletin_board/5/messages/1157.html]. 

===Noun===
'''[[parting]] [[shot]]'''
#{{idiom}} An [[insult]] or barbed comment issued as the speaker departs or the conversation comes to an end.
#*'''2007'''. "Gold Coast Deputy Mayor David Power took a parting shot at the Crime and Misconduct Commission and his council enemies as he announced his bombshell resignation today." "Power's parting shot at enemies", Greg Stolz, the Courier-Mail [http://www.news.com.au/couriermail/story/0,20797,22439887-3102,00.html?from=public_rss].